<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idab855a8f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s9801"><num value="9801">§ 9801.</num><heading> Definition</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this chapter, the term “settle” means consider, ascertain, adjust, determine, and dispose of a claim, whether by full or partial allowance or by disallowance.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idab855a90-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(<ref href="/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041">Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/70A/591">70A Stat. 591</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/100/180/dA/tXII/s1231/19/B">Pub. L. 100–180, div. A, title XII, § 1231(19)(B)</ref>, <date date="1987-12-04">Dec. 4, 1987</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/101/1161">101 Stat. 1161</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
